# Billing Rules

## Purpose
Razorpay subscriptions per `docs/BILLING_SPEC.md` and BR-B* business rules.

## Requirements
- Plans: basic, pro, enterprise with limits enforced at API layer.
- Webhook HMAC verification; idempotent by `razorpay_event_id`.
- Subscription states: trialing, active, past_due, suspended, cancelled.
- past_due > 7 days triggers org suspended read-only mode.
- Invoices generated async; PDF to S3; email billing_email.
- Upgrade immediate with proration; downgrade at period end.

## Restrictions
- No storing Razorpay secret in code or logs.
- No activating tenant without confirmed webhook or verified checkout.
- No manual SQL subscription edits without audit.

## Best Practices
- Dedicated `billing-webhooks` queue concurrency 1 per tenant.
- Expose upgrade CTA in `QUOTA_EXCEEDED` error payload.
- Test mode keys only in dev/staging.

## Anti-Patterns
- Trusting client-reported payment success without webhook.
- Double-charging on webhook retry without idempotency.

## Examples

```typescript
if (await this.webhookRepo.exists(eventId)) return { ok: true };
await this.subscriptionService.activateFromWebhook(payload);
await this.webhookRepo.markProcessed(eventId);
```
